result.execSummary:
The defendant Braxton Tyler Brooks was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Braxton Tyler Brooks in court.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called @ 1:46 p.m. Waiver of atty and plea quest. forms filed. Court reviews atty waiver. Court finds waiver freely & voluntarily made. Agreement stated - Def will plead to charge, State will recommend $50 plus costs. Def agrees. No contest plea. Court reviews plea quest. and constitutional rights. Court finds plea freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts plea and finds guilty of possession of drug paraphernalia. Def has question regarding record. Nothing else by Def. Court approves agreement. $50 plus costs, including DNA surcharge and sample. Def advised to report for booking and DNA sample.  DNA colloquy.  Def will pay today and pp for traffic citation. Court will allow pp for any balance unable to pay today. Postconviction rights. Court vacates warrant authorization. State advises Def's letter said to appear at 1:30 p.m.

Defendant Braxton Tyler Brooks not in court.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls  @ 9:32 am.  State request warrant, 500 cash bond. Court authorize warrant $500.00, 15TR490 Court finds def. Guilty by Default & orders 175.30 & 60 days to pay.
